    "- Control de calidad.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Modelado estadÃ­stico.\n",
    "\n",
    "## DistribuciÃ³n Normal\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "La distribuciÃ³n normal tiene **dos parÃ¡metros**: $\\mu$ y $\\sigma$. AquÃ­, $\\mu$ puede ser cualquier nÃºmero y $\\sigma$ puede ser cualquier nÃºmero positivo.\n",
    "\n",
    "La funciÃ³n de [**densidad de probabilidad**]{style=\"color: #4682B4\"} de una distribuciÃ³n normal con media $\\mu$ y varianza $\\sigma^2$ estÃ¡ dada por\n",
    "\n",
    "$$f(x)= \\frac{1}{\\sigma\\sqrt{2 \\pi}} e^{\\frac{-(x-\\mu)^2}{2\\sigma^2}},\\; -\\infty<x<\\infty.$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Si $X$ sigue una distribuciÃ³n normal con media $\\mu$ y varianza $\\sigma^2$, escribimos $X\\sim{N(\\mu,\\sigma^2)}$.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "##\n",
    "\n",
    "</br></br>\n",
    "\n",
    "![](images/clipboard-4081450505.png){fig-align=\"center\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Media y varianza\n",
    "\n",
    "</br></br>\n",
    "\n",
    "Si $X\\sim{N(\\mu,\\sigma^2)}$, entonces\n",
    "\n",
    "- El promedio teÃ³rico de $X$ es $\\mu$.\n",
    "\n",
    "- La varianza teÃ³rica de $X$ es $\\sigma^2$.\n",
    "\n",
    "- La desviaciÃ³n estÃ¡ndar teÃ³rica de $X$ es $\\sigma$.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Efecto de los parametros\n",
